{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "962ce6374bc1db0c", "candidate": {"id": "cand-004", "name": "Sarah-Jane Whitmore", "raw_cv": "SARAH-JANE WHITMORE\nsj.whitmore@email.com | London, UK\n\nSENIOR PRODUCT MANAGER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nProduct leader with 8 years of experience in B2B SaaS, focused on PLG and self-serve growth. Track record of scaling products from Series A to Series C. Experienced people manager and cross-functional leader.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nHead of Product \u2014 Workato (Remote, UK) (2022\u2013present)\n- Led a team of 4 PMs across integration and automation product lines\n- Drove 40% ARR growth on the self-serve tier through PLG experiments and activation improvements\n- Partnered with GTM to define ICP and build product-led sales motion\n\nSenior Product Manager \u2014 Spendesk, London (2019\u20132022)\n- Owned the expense management and approval workflow product\n- Shipped automated receipt matching, reducing manual finance team work by 5 hours/week per customer\n- Introduced Mixpanel and built the company's first product analytics framework\n\nProduct Manager \u2014 Trello (Atlassian), London (2017\u20132019)\n- PM for the Power-Ups marketplace; grew active integrations by 120 in 12 months\n\nSKILLS\nProduct-led growth, B2B SaaS, OKRs, roadmapping, user research, SQL, Amplitude, Mixpanel, Figma, people management, enterprise sales partnership\n\nEDUCATION\nMEng Computer Science \u2014 University of Cambridge (2013\u20132017)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen", "raw_linkedin": "Product leader obsessed with building B2B SaaS products that sell themselves. I've spent eight years in workflow automation and spend management software \u2014 from Series A scrappiness to Series C scale. Currently leading product at Workato UK, where I have a team of four PMs and we're building the self-serve motion from scratch. I love PLG, data, and the puzzle of making enterprise software actually delightful. Remote-first but occasionally in London co-working spaces. Open to Head of Product or VP Product roles at growth-stage B2B companies.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Sarah-Jane, thanks for joining us. Tell me about your approach to PLG at Workato.\n\nSarah-Jane: At Workato we had a traditional sales-led model and I was brought in to build a PLG layer alongside it. The first thing I did was run activation experiments \u2014 we had a 14-day trial that most users weren't getting value from in time. We redesigned the first-run experience using data from Amplitude and cut time-to-first-automation from 4 days to 20 minutes. That unlocked a 40% lift in trial-to-paid conversion.\n\nInterviewer: How do you manage your team?\n\nSarah-Jane: I have four direct reports \u2014 three senior PMs and one associate PM I've been mentoring. I focus on clarity of ownership, ambitious but achievable goals, and creating space for them to think strategically rather than just executing tickets. I do monthly strategy sessions with the team and quarterly offsites when we can.\n\nInterviewer: This is a fully remote role. How do you feel about that?\n\nSarah-Jane: I've been remote since 2020 and it suits me very well. I have a proper home office setup and I'm very comfortable running async-first teams. I occasionally work from co-working spaces for the social element, but I don't need to be in an office.\n\nInterviewer: Are you UK based with right to work?\n\nSarah-Jane: Yes, British citizen, no issues there.\n\nInterviewer: And salary?\n\nSarah-Jane: I'm at \u00a392,000 currently. I'd be looking for \u00a395,000 for this role.", "years_experience": 8.0, "skills": ["product-led growth", "B2B SaaS", "OKRs", "roadmapping", "user research", "SQL", "Amplitude", "Mixpanel", "Figma", "people management", "enterprise sales partnership", "workflow automation", "spend management", "product analytics", "data-driven decision making"], "industries": ["SaaS", "workflow automation", "spend management", "integration platforms"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": true, "education_level": "master", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.88, "culture_fit_score": 0.82, "constraints": [{"id": "93569aa5", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Candidate seeking minimum salary of \u00a395,000 for new role", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 95000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "7974a657", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Candidate's current salary is \u00a392,000 (reference point)", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 92000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "8438626a", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Requires fully remote working; has been remote since 2020 and is very comfortable with async-first teams", "canonical_key": "remote_ok", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.97, "currency": null}, {"id": "d141999d", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "visa", "description": "British citizen with right to work in UK; no visa sponsorship required", "canonical_key": "visa_sponsorship", "value": false, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": null}, {"id": "fa310db6", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "role", "description": "Open to Head of Product or VP Product roles at growth-stage B2B companies", "canonical_key": null, "value": "Head of Product or VP Product", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 0.85, "confidence": 0.9, "currency": null}, {"id": "dc3669b2", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "industry_background", "description": "Prefers growth-stage B2B SaaS companies; strong track record Series A to Series C scaling", "canonical_key": "industry_background", "value": "B2B SaaS growth-stage", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 0.9, "confidence": 0.